    <item>
      <title>Raymond James Stadium</title>
      <link>http://localhost:53390/tracks/raymond-james-stadium/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:53390/tracks/raymond-james-stadium/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Stadium Overview 
    &lt;div id=&#34;stadium-overview&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#stadium-overview&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Raymond James Stadium, affectionately known as &amp;ldquo;Ray Jay&amp;rdquo; by locals, serves as one of the premier venues on the Monster Energy AMA Supercross circuit. Home to the NFL&amp;rsquo;s Tampa Bay Buccaneers, this impressive facility transforms into a world-class Supercross battleground each season, challenging riders with its unique Florida conditions and typically technical track designs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Snapdragon Stadium</title>
      <link>http://localhost:53390/tracks/san-diego-snapdragon-stadium/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:53390/tracks/san-diego-snapdragon-stadium/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The New Home of San Diego Supercross 
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-new-home-of-san-diego-supercross&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#the-new-home-of-san-diego-supercross&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Snapdragon Stadium represents the newest chapter in San Diego&amp;rsquo;s long and storied Supercross history. Opened in 2022, this state-of-the-art facility has taken over from the historic Qualcomm/Jack Murphy Stadium (demolished in 2021) as Southern California&amp;rsquo;s premier Supercross venue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
